main event: A small, round, extremely high, white-clear object was observed in the sky for about 2 minutes near Tallassee, Alabama on May 19, 1960.
interesting points: The object sometimes appeared bright and shiny.
The object faded away in a fog.
The weather was clear with no clouds visible.
There were no known aircraft or balloons in the area at the time.
The observer was cutting grass when they noticed the object in the sky.
sighted object: small, round, extremely high, white-clear object
